Dialogue: 10,0:00:26.77,0:00:33.79,Default,,0,0,0,,EDO, Retklaad Disasmount has completed\N his mission and safely returned from Fedvar. {レトクラード・ディザーズマウント\N / フェドバー}{Retklaad - there's no official translation, so I kept this from the original subs, plus it sounds badass}
Dialogue: 10,0:00:33.79,0:00:37.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Well done, Retklaad.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:37.17,0:00:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course. I'm glad I was able to be of service.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:40.72,0:00:43.08,Default,,0,0,0,,This has been a blessing in disguise.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:43.08,0:00:49.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks to this accident, we can now definitely prevent\N the destruction of Fedvar's environment.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:49.74,0:00:52.43,Default,,0,0,0,,EDO should be pleased with that.{dc: he's talking to edo}
Dialogue: 10,0:00:52.43,0:00:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,EDO, in light of recent events, we'd like\N to appoint a new administrator to Fedvar.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:58.44,0:01:04.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand. We shall select\N the most fitting candidate by tomorrow.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:04.82,0:01:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:14.05,0:01:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Really though, that was excellent work, Retklaad.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:18.08,0:01:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,No. All I did was fulfill my duty, that's all.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:23.38,0:01:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure, but that duty wasn't for the faint of heart.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:26.22,0:01:30.66,Default,,0,0,0,,But you did it for the good of the world\N and its people. I hope you know that.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:30.66,0:01:31.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I do.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:31.82,0:01:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, Retklaad, are you sure this\N won't be discovered later?
Dialogue: 10,0:01:36.94,0:01:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Please don't worry about that.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:38.72,0:01:42.60,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no evidence to use against me.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:43.35,0:01:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,EDO's system is safe, for now. \NLet's hurry up and forget about Fedvar.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:48.55,0:01:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, look at that.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:50.29,0:01:52.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The cherry trees are in full bloom.{sakura are cherry trees, not cherries}
Dialogue: 10,0:01:52.14,0:01:55.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Throughout the ages, the cherry blossoms\N have retained their beauty.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:55.71,0:02:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Speaking of cherry blossoms, \Nhow is your oh-so-beloved son Gold doing, Retklaad?{dc: i tried}
Dialogue: 10,0:02:01.48,0:02:04.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Your sarcasm is obvious.{damn, Perevo worded something cool by mistake}
Dialogue: 10,0:02:04.05,0:02:06.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I disowned him five years ago.{It's been five years since I disowned him.}{changed for cps}
Dialogue: 10,0:02:06.51,0:02:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,By now, he's probably dying a dog's death\N by the roadside somewhere. {dying by the roadside; dying a dog's death}
Dialogue: 10,0:02:23.05,0:02:27.24,Narrator,,0,0,0,,This era is ruled by a massive\N{dc: says kyodai} computer named EDO.{dc: no clue how to word this sono jidai shit, gonna just put it in present tense}{***maybe: This is an era rules by an enormous computer named EDO,}
Dialogue: 10,0:02:27.24,0:02:33.20,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Constructed through international cooperation,\N it connects Japan's cities and space colonies.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:33.20,0:02:37.14,Narrator,,0,0,0,,EDO's job is to decide on the best policy\N for a given situation.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:37.14,0:02:40.76,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Its work is overseen by five consuls.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:57.91,0:02:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,What's going on?!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:06.29,0:03:07.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-Who are you?!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:08.18,0:03:10.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Retklaad Disasmount...
Dialogue: 10,0:03:10.63,0:03:14.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The graveyard of the cosmos brought me\N back to life as a vengeful spirit.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:15.22,0:03:17.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-You... It can't be!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:18.94,0:03:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Die!
